V ligi nastopa 20 klubov, kjer vsako sezono nekdo postane prvak in izpade v špansko drugo ligo. Najuspešnejša kluba sta madridski Real in Barcelona. Skupaj sta ligo osvojila kar 56-krat. programme.desc: Crvena zvezda bo s pomočjo polnega stadiona Rajka Mitića, bolj poznan pod imenom Marakana, lovila uvrstitev v skupinski del Evropske lige. Krasnodar je prvo tekmo dobil s 3:2, vendar daleč od tega, da bi si lahko privoščil mirno pot v Beograd. Rdeče-beli so odločeni spreobrniti izid in poskrbeti, da bodo v srbski prestolnici tudi jeseni spremljali evropski nogomet

programme.title: Spanish league: Real Madrid - Valencia
programme.desc: Madridski Real bo uvodni del prvenstva odigral brez Cristiana Ronalda, ki bo zaradi odrivanja sodnika na prvi tekmi španskega superpokala proti Barceloni počival na štirih prvenstvenih obračunih (skupno petih), vseeno pa bi morali galaktiki tudi brez njega pridno nabirati točke. Valencia je sicer v preteklosti že znala prekrižati načrte Realu. Lahko netopirji tudi tokrat pripravijo presenečenje?

programme.title: Portugal liga: Sporting - Estoril
programme.desc: Nekoč Primeira Liga, danes Liga NOS je najelitnejše nogometno tekmovanje na Portugalskem. V njej vsako leto sodeluje 18 klubov, vendar le pet je takšnih, ki so jo od leta 1934 (datum ustanovitve) tudi osvojili. Kar 81 od skupnih 83 naslovov je osvojila t.i. velika trojica (Benfica, Sporting in Porto) preostala dva naslova pa sta romala v roke Belenensesa in Boaviste. Aktualni prvaki so nogometaši Benfice

programme.title: Serbian League: Crvena zvezda - Partizan

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2007 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2007 All-Star Game in Las Vegas. The West crushed the East 153-132 as Kobe Bryant earned MVP honors. It was the first time the game was played in a city without an NBA franchise. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2008 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2008 All-Star Game in New Orleans. The East won 132-128, behind LeBron James' 27 points and second MVP award in three years. In the win, Ray Allen scored 14 of his game-high 28 points in the fourth quarter. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2009 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2009 All-Star Game in Phoenix. Suns center Shaquille O'Neal and his former Lakers teammate Kobe Bryant shared MVP honors in a 146-119 win for the West. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2010 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2010 All-Star Game in Arlington, Texas. A record throng of over 108,000 witnessed the East's 141-139 victory, with Dwyane Wade taking MVP honors. Derrick Rose and Kevin Durant made debuts. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2011 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2011 All-Star Game in Los Angeles. Kobe Bryant nabbed his fourth MVP award in a 148-143 West victory. Blake Griffin and Kevin Love made debuts. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2012 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2012 All-Star Game in Orlando. Kevin Durant earned MVP honors as the West won for a second straight year, 152-149. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2013 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2013 All-Star Game in Houston. Chris Paul took home MVP honors as the West outscored the East for the third straight year. Kevin Durant tallied a game-high 30 points. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2014 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2014 NBA All-Star Game in New Orleans. Kyrie Irving was named MVP as the East snapped a three-year drought vs. the West. Stephen Curry (starter), Damian Lillard, Paul Millsap, Anthony Davis, DeMar DeRozan and John Wall made their debuts. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2015 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2015 All-Star Game at Madison Square Garden. Russell Westbrook won MVP honors for the victorious West. (cc)

programme.title: NBA Hardwood Classics: 2016 All-Star Game
programme.desc: The 2016 All-Star Game in Toronto. Russell Westbrook took MVP honors for the second straight year, as the West romped by 23 points. First-time stars included Kawhi Leonard, Draymond Green, Andre Drummond and Isaiah Thomas. (cc)
